revision.text:
''' [[Strømsgodset IF|Strømsgodset]]'''  won the Norwegian Cup after beating [[FC Lyn Oslo|Lyn]] 4&ndash;2 on 25 October. The goal scorers for Strømsgodset were [[Thorodd Presberg]] who scored in the 30th and 46th minutes, and Ingar Pettersen who scored in the 67th and 69th minute. For Lyn, Trygve Christophersen scored in the 10th and 37th minutes.<br />     25&nbsp;744 spectators watched the game at [[Ullevål stadion]] in [[Oslo]]. The referee was [[Einar Røed]]. This was the second time Strømsgodset won the Norwegian Cup.

'''Strømsgodset's winning squad:''' [[Inge Thun]], [[Arild Mathisen]], [[Jan Kristiansen]], [[Tor Alsaker-Nøstdahl]], [[Erik Eriksen]], [[Odd Arild Amundsen]], [[Egil H. Olsen]], [[Bjørn Odmar Andersen]], [[Steinar Pettersen]], [[Thorodd Presberg]], [[Ingar Pettersen (footballer)|Ingar Pettersen]]; 
[[Ole Johnny Friise]], [[Håvard Beckstrøm]], [[Johnny Vidar Pedersen]], [[Sverre Rørvik]] and [[Per Rune Wølner]].

'''Lyn's team:''' [[Svein Bjørn Olsen]], [[Jan Rodvang]], [[Helge Østvold]], [[Tore Børrehaug]],
[[Knut Kolle]], [[Arild Gulden]], [[Andreas Morisbak]], [[Ola Dybwad-Olsen]], [[Sven Otto Birkeland]], [[Trygve Christophersen]] and [[Jon Palmer Austnes]].

