{{infobox country at games|NOC=AUS|NOCname=[[Australian Olympic Committee]]|games=Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games|year=2017|date=17–27 September|flagcaption=|oldcode=|website={{url|}}|location=[[Ashgabat]]|competitors=17|sports=3|flagbearer=|rank=|gold=0|silver=0|bronze=2|officials=|appearances=|seealso=}}
'''[[Australia]]''' competed at the [[2017 Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games]] held in [[Ashgabat]], [[Turkmenistan]] from September 17 to 27. 17 athletes competed in 3 different sports.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ashgabat2017.com/results/aus|title=Australia {{!}} The 5th Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games - 2017|last=|first=|date=|website=ashgabat2017.com|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ashgabat2017.com/news/2017-06-29T1801-Awstraliya-Ashgabat-2017-a-gatnashjak-18-turgenini-saylady-|title=Australia select 18 athletes to compete at Ashgabat 2017 {{!}} Latest News {{!}} Ashgabat 2017|website=ashgabat2017.com|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ocasia.org/Game/GameParticular.aspx?9QoyD9QEWPdkzAjI/K7uyA==|title=Olympic Council of Asia : Games|website=www.ocasia.org|access-date=2017-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171212124624/http://www.ocasia.org/Game/GameParticular.aspx?9QoyD9QEWPdkzAjI%2FK7uyA=%3D|archive-date=2017-12-12|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
Australia made its debut in an [[Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games]] for the first time at the Games held in [[Turkmenistan]] along with other [[Oceania]] nations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/blog/2017/sep/17/repression-raids-sport-turkmenistan-asian-games-tyranny|title=IOC turns a blind eye to Turkmenistan using sport to legitimise tyranny {{!}} Kieran Pender|last=Pender|first=Kieran|date=2017-09-17|work=The Guardian|access-date=2017-10-11|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.euronews.com/2017/09/17/game-on-for-ashgabat-and-fifth-asian-indoor-and-martial-arts-games|title=Game on for Ashgabat and Fifth Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games|date=2017-09-17|work=euronews|access-date=2017-10-11|language=en}}</ref>
