'''Inter Club d'Escaldes''' is an Andorran [[association football|football]] club based in [[Escaldes-Engordany]]. The club currently plays in [[Primera Divisió]].

== History ==
'''Inter Club d'Escaldes''' was founded in [[Escaldes-Engordany]] in 1991 and being founder member of [[Primera Divisió]] in 1995, the Premier League of Andorra. The club was playing since then in the top flight until April 2015 when the team was relegated after finishing 8th in the regular league.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.faf.ad/pnfg/NNws_ShwNewDup?codigo=1005950&cod_primaria=3000301&cod_secundaria=3000301#.VTUy0ZNv1S4|title=FAF - L'FC Santa Coloma dóna un cop sobre la taula en endur-se el derbi ciutadà|author=|date=|website=www.faf.ad|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref> The club returned in Primera Divisió after two seasons, in May 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elperiodic.ad/noticia/58075/tic-tapa-i-ue-santa-coloma-seran-a-europa-i-linter-es-de-primera|title=Tic Tapa i UE Santa Coloma seran a Europa i l’Inter és de Primera|author=|date=|website=elperiodic.ad|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref>

''L'Inter'' achieved twice the third position in [[Primera Divisió]], during two consecutives seasons in 1999-00 and 2000–01, and became runners-up in [[Copa Constitució]] during the 2001–02 season, losing 2–0 against [[FC Lusitanos]].

==Colors and badge==
In its beginnings the club had a strong support of ''Construccions Modernes'', a company linked to the construction, to the point that its initials ''CM'' remain until the present time in its shield. Due to team colors, blue and black, the team and fans are referenced as ''blau-i-negres''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elperiodic.ad/noticia/57373/la-faf-es-posa-dura-per-lencesa-duna-bengala-a-la-borda-mateu|title=La FAF es posa dura per l’encesa d’una bengala a la Borda Mateu|author=|date=|website=elperiodic.ad|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref>
