{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}} {{Use British English|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Royal Air Force Sports Ground | nickname = Vine Lane<ref>[http://www.middlesexccc.com/content_default.asp?ContentID=10 Other name]</ref> | country = England | image = | location = [[Uxbridge]], [[Middlesex]] | establishment = 1939 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year2 = | club2 = | year1 = 1964 | club1 = [[Combined Services cricket team|Combined Services]] | date = 22 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/808.html CricketArchive }}
The '''Royal Air Force Sports Ground''' is a cricket ground in [[Uxbridge]], situated behind [[RAF Uxbridge]]. The ground also goes by the name of '''Vine Lane''', a nearby main road. It was first used in 1939 by the [[Royal Air Force cricket team|RAF]]. Teams such as the [[Marylebone Cricket Club|MCC]], the [[Middlesex Cricket Board]], the [[British Army cricket team|Army]], Middlesex youth teams and the [[Combined Services cricket team|Combined Services]] have all played on the ground throughout its history. The ground has seen one [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match, in 1964, between the Combined Services and [[Cambridge University Cricket Club|Cambridge University]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/26/26804.html Combined Services v Cambridge University, 1964]</ref>
