{{Infobox_Stadium | stadium_name = Sports Hall Diana | nickname = | image = [[File:Yambol-Diana-hall.jpg|300px]] | location = [[Yambol]], [[Bulgaria]] | broke_ground = | opened = 1964 | renovated = | owner = Yambol Municipality | construction_cost = | architect = | tenants = [[BC Yambol]] | seating_capacity = 3000 }} '''Diana Hall''' ({{lang-bg|'''Зала "Диана"'''}}) is a multifunctional [[Indoor arena]] in [[Yambol]], [[Bulgaria]]. The arena was opened in 1964 and has a seating capacity for 3,000 people . It is the home of [[BC Yambol]]. Besides [[basketball]] the arena is used for practicing [[trampolining]], [[boxing]], [[wrestling]], [[shooting sport]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sportuvai.bg/%D0%97%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B0-%D0%94%D0%B8%D0%B0%D0%BD%D0%B0-_l.sp_i.9604.html |title=Зала „Диана” |website=Sportuvai.bg |date= |accessdate=2016-01-29}}</ref> The arena hosted many national and European tournaments, such as the 2010 [[Bulgarian Basketball Cup]], [[National Basketball League (Bulgaria)|NBL]] all-star game 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.all-star.bg/gallery/prestige-all-star-game-2015|title=Prestige All Star Game 2015 - Престиж Мач на звездите 2015 - All Star Game|website=All-star.bg|accessdate=2016-01-29}}</ref> [[Strandzha Cup]], international wrestling tournament Dan Kolov.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yambolbasketball.com/arena/diana-arena.php|title=THIS IS "DIANA" Arena - home of Yambol BASKETBALL|website=Yambolbasketball.com|accessdate=2016-01-29}}</ref>
