{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Vista Road Recreation Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Clacton-on-Sea]], [[Essex]] | establishment = 1931 <small>(first recorded match)</small> | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1931–1966 | club1 = [[Essex County Cricket Club|Essex]] | date = 11 September | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/417.html CricketArchive }}
'''Vista Road Recreation Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Clacton-on-Sea]], [[Essex]]. The first recorded [[first-class cricket]] match on the ground was in 1931 when [[Essex County Cricket Club]] played there against [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire]]. Essex played a total of 60 first-class matches on the ground between 1931 and 1966, playing their final first-class match there against [[Leicestershire County Cricket Club|Leicestershire]] in the [[1966 English cricket season|1966 County Championship]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/417_f.html First-Class Matches played on Vista Road Recreation Ground], CricketArchive. Retrieved 2016-11-10.</ref>
The ground has also held five Second XI fixtures between 1948 and 1952 for the Essex Second XI in the [[Minor Counties Championship]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/417_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on Vista Road Recreation Ground], CricketArchive. Retrieved 2016-11-10.</ref>
In local cricket, the ground is the home venue of [[Clacton Cricket Club]].
